stream
BT /F1 10 Tf 50 780 Td 13 TL
(ACME DRIVES VFD-2000 SERIES - INSTALLATION & TROUBLESHOOTING MANUAL) Tj T*
(Section 6: Fault Codes and Corrective Actions) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FAULT CODE TABLE:) Tj T*
(F0A1 Overvoltage - DC bus above limit. Check supply, decel time.) Tj T*
(F0B2 Undervoltage - DC bus below limit. Check supply, loose terminals.) Tj T*
(F0C1 Overcurrent - Output current exceeded 200% of drive rating.) Tj T*
(F0D3 Overtemperature - Heatsink above limit. Check fans and filters.) Tj T*
(F0E4 Ground fault - Leakage current detected. Megger motor and cable.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(F0C1 OVERCURRENT - DETAILS:) Tj T*
(Possible causes:) Tj T*
(1. Mechanical jam or blockage on the driven load) Tj T*
(2. Motor overload \(excessive material load, belt drag\)) Tj T*
(3. Short circuit in motor cable or terminal box) Tj T*
(4. Loose power wiring at drive output or motor terminals) Tj T*
(5. Failed motor bearing causing mechanical drag) Tj T*
(6. Acceleration time set too short for load inertia) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Corrective actions:) Tj T*
(- Inspect the driven equipment for jams before resetting) Tj T*
(- Verify motor current against nameplate FLA) Tj T*
(- Check output wiring and motor terminal tightness) Tj T*
(- Review acceleration/deceleration parameters \(P2.03 / P2.04\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(WARNING: Do not reset the drive repeatedly after F0C1.) Tj T*
(Repeated resets into a fault can damage the drive and motor.) Tj T*
(If the fault returns after one reset, isolate and investigate.) Tj T*
ET
endstream
